ClearOne, Inc. Key Developments

ClearOne Introduces Two New Expander Solutions for CONVERGE Pro 2 DSP Mixers
Jun 13 17
ClearOne is introducing a duo of compact yet powerful interface expanders —CONVERGE® Pro 2 USB and CONVERGE Pro 2 GPIO — that increase the number of ports available for conferencing connectivity and room control for all CONVERGE Pro 2 DS mixers. The new CONVERGE® Pro 2 USB and CONVERGE Pro 2 GPIO expanders -- USB connectivity and room-control options for all CONVERGE Pro 2 DS mixers. The USB expander acts primarily as a USB audio interface, connecting a laptop directly to the room's professional-quality audio with familiar PC-based video conferencing applications, including ClearOne Spontania, Google® Hangouts, Skype® for Business, WebEx®, or any other cloud-based applications. It also can be used to share the DSP mixer resources across multiple rooms. The GPIO Expander provides a dozen input and output pins to control in-room devices such as microphones, cameras, window coverings, and lights. As many as 3 USB expanders and 3 GPIO expanders can be daisy-chained per CONVERGE Pro 2 mixer — in any order — to further increase USB connectivity and room-control options. The new CONVERGE Pro 2 Expanders are shipping at the end of August 2017.


ClearOne Introduces CONVERGE Amplifiers
Jun 12 17
ClearOne, Inc. announced two new, Class-D four-channel power amplifiers, CONVERGE PA. The compact, 1-RU size power amplifiers are loaded with exceptionally flexible features that are the last word in plug-and-play architecture — having phased out the usual configuration software and delivering the simplicity integrators need. ClearOne's new CONVERGE PA 4120 (featuring four channels at 120 watts) and CONVERGE PA 460 (four channels at 60 watts) are optimized to excel with ClearOne DSP products, such as CONVERGE Pro 2 and 1, and INTERACT® Pro, as well as with third-party DSP mixers. CONVERGE PA's other top-line features include: Balanced line inputs for all channels; 8 Ohms and 70- and 100-volt output modes; User-selectable manual switches for advanced settings, such as input gain, high-pass filter, and standby; Amplifier and speaker protection from short circuits, overload, high temperatures, and clipping; Clear front-panel indicators for protection, standby, input, and output signals; Auto-standby mode for efficient power consumption; A DC power backup option for emergency system applications. The new CONVERGE PA Amplifiers are shipping at the end of the third quarter of 2017.


ClearOne Introduces VIEW Pro 4K
Jun 12 17
ClearOne, has introduced VIEW Pro 4K, a new line of 4K-capable, IP-based, multimedia streaming products. Consisting of the E110 4K Encoder and D110 4K Decoder, VIEW Pro 4K employs both H.264 lossless compression and H.265 high-efficiency video coding compression, supports 4K resolution at 60 FPS, and provides integrators and end-users with a uniquely customizable, scalable, and affordable 4K multimedia streaming solution. The company will debut the new line at InfoComm (Booth 3421), June 14-16 in Orlando. The flexibility and scalability of IP network-based distribution, combined with ClearOne's built-in software license technology, has made it the preferred distribution method for audio and video installations in just about every industry – from corporate boardrooms to schools and universities, in security command and control centers, in hospitality, healthcare, retail and more. The VIEW Pro 4K lineup increases the depth and capabilities of ClearOne's existing View Pro products, offering unique combination of standard features, proprietary technology, and customizable software licenses that include video-wall, video windowing, and video-composition capabilities. The software is built in to the products and can be activated at any time, if and when needed, for a one-time, per-device fee. ClearOne's HD VIEW Pro 4K products deliver 4:4:4, 24-bit color multimedia streaming and can accept a variety of video signal types, formats and resolutions and seamlessly distribute them over an existing IP network. The new VIEW Pro E110 4K and D110 4K are shipping at the end of August 2017.


